_data.text:
## Reusablity

As you can see, the Monorepository has anything bundled, when it comes to a Web 3 Project. If you do your own project, you can share yours as a template, which benefits to the ecosystem.

### Component and Module Ecosystem

Share your ready to use client components and node modules, so other applications could use that. Few sections of other apps could need your service! For deeper insights [have a look here at Ecosystem Concept](/ecosystem/concept)

### Cli

Put your project structure into the template folders, remove your content and publish it to **npm**. The script is already done for you. So others can simply do

```bash
npx create-<Your Project Name>-app <Others Project Name>
```

#### Example

You made a Shop out of `npx create-ecosis-app web3shop`

By replacing the *Templates Repository* Content and publishing it to **npm** (you need to have an account) with `npm publish --access public` others can simple use it by

```bash
npx create-web3shop-app <New Project Name>
```

Thats it!

_data.text:
## Requirements

For developing your own Web 3 Application out of the box, you need to be experienced with

- HTML
- CSS
- Typescript/Javascript
- Solidity (optional)

This environments need to be used for developing, building and deploying your project:

- NodeJS with *npm* or *yarn*
- Harthat or Truffle (optional)

***If you dont want to do it programmatically, stay tuned for the deployer and hoster coming until end of this year!***

## Quick Start

> Hint: If you dont want to develop a hole Web 3 Application but just a simple classic Application go ahead over to [enjine](https://enjine.ecosis,io)

```bash
npx create-ecosis-app <Your Project>
```

## Overview

> Ofcourse, you are free to use only parts - there is no need to use it as a hole, if you are interested in other client technologies like React instead of Vue, Bootstrapp instead of TailwindCSS and so on. If you want a more cleaner and basic version have a look [here in 'Configuration'](/developer/config)

### Project Directory Structure

```
./project
  /app
  /contracts
  /docs
  /home
  /packages
    /cli
    /common
    /components
    /nuxt
```

_data.text:
## What is Web 3

Web 3 is the next generation of Web, which is made by the community for the community. *Just for imagination:*

- Web 1 - Companies, Institutions etc make the content and earn out of it
- Web 2 - Companies, Institutions deliver platforms, so user and communities make the content and the Companies and Institutions earn out of it
- Web 3 - (Permissionless Web) Users and communities delivers platforms, so user and communities make the content and the they all earn out of it by their own!

This is all possible due ***Distributed Ledger Technologies*** (known as *Blockchain*), because this ships reliable transparency and data security. Thanks to ***Smart Contracts***, which is runnable code on the blockchain, data processing can be done by programmatical logic. For examples tokens to exchange values (sometimes called *coins* or *tokens*) or store data in a trustworthy and secure way (social media, asset management etc).

However, Web 3 is permissionless, which means users and organizations can participate by their own without censorship by one authority. This gives user the absolute freeness to share data and values by their own. The authority is made by the hole network itself and not by one entity or instance, so its *decentralized*. You are free to use any network you trust.

Its the most democratic way to do web!

Recently common use-cases are

- Decentralized Autonomous Organizations
- Decentralized Finance

## What is Tokenomics

The word **Tokenomics** is formed of two words *Token* and *Economics*, which means ***the economics of tokens***. 

Disciplines are economical fundamentals like, when to *mint*, *burn*, *distribute* tokens (acts like a currency) and more to have a stable economics between entities.
